quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  43,26,"And [remember] when Abraham said to his father and his people, “I disown all that you worship"
  43,27,except the One Who created me; He will surely guide me.”
  43,28,"And he made it a lasting word among his descendants, so that they may return [to Allah]"
  43,29,"However, I let these [Makkans] and their forefathers enjoy their lives, until there came to them the truth and a clear messenger"
  43,30,"But when the truth came to them, they said, “This is magic, and we definitely reject it.”"
  43,31,"And they said, “Why was this Qur’an not sent down to a great man from one of the two towns?”"
  43,32,"Is it they who distribute the mercy of your Lord? It is We Who have distributed their livelihood among them in the life of this world, and have raised some of them above others in ranks, so that they may serve one another. But the mercy of your Lord is better than what they accumulate"
  43,33,"Were it not that all people might become a single community [of disbelievers], We would have given those who disbelieve in the Most Compassionate houses of sliver roofs and staircases to ascend"
  43,34,"and their houses having [silver] doors and couches on which they recline"
  43,35,"and [golden] ornaments. But all of these are mere enjoyments of the life of this world, and the Hereafter with your Lord is [only] for those who fear Allah"